TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {3663=The 1977 San Francisco Giants season was the Giants' 95th season in Major League Baseball, their 20th season in San Francisco since their move from New York following the 1957 season, and their 18th at Candlestick Park. The team finished in fourth place in the National League West with an 75-87 record, 23 games behind the Los Angesles Dodgers.}
